they saw things. What the problems were.

03:45.441 --> 03:49.387
What did he think of the changes that you made? He 
was formed.

03:54.655 --> 03:56.538
And he felt that you were improving morale? Yes.

04:00.837 --> 04:11.773
That

04:00.837 --> 04:11.773
was a major problem? Oh, in the States, in the Air 
Force, you know, in all the services.

04:23.850 --> 04:25.713
That was the only incident that you had? The only 
incident I had was in the Air Force. Of

04:29.525 --> 04:46.977
course, during this time, Europe has sort of taken 
a second place to war in Vietnam, and did- I thought

04:47.665 --> 05:03.279
that there was a tremendous buildup in Southeast 
Asia, and of course a decrease in supplies and

04:47.665 --> 05:03.279
troops in Europe. Did that have an impact on you and 
the Azores?

05:11.847 --> 05:17.352
I don't think it did, except it slowed down the 
amount of traffic that's come through. Several

05:17.855 --> 05:19.919
big exercises every year. Came through. A lot of 
deployments. Rapid deployments.

05:31.120 --> 05:31.360
Sure. And did you ever have missions or training 
exercises with the Portuguese?

05:40.778 --> 05:40.858
Yes. Unless

05:42.610 --> 05:59.594
they

05:42.610 --> 05:59.594
had

05:42.610 --> 05:59.594
a very small air force. Oh, yes. They only had C-54 
and a couple other small airplanes there. That's

